post_text:
Developmental Screenings
September 30, 2020
By Appointment only

The Cosmopolis School District will offer FREE developmental screenings for Cosmopolis resident children from birth through 5 years of age, on September 30, 2020 and will be scheduled from 8:30 to 10:30 a.m. If your family is living in a temporary situation, you may contact the district where you are staying to attend a screening. Parents with concerns for children ages 5 to 21, may contact the school office any time, to schedule a screening for their child.
The purpose of the screening is to assist parents who may have concerns about their child's development. The screenings will help identify potential problems which may affect the child's success in school, and will indicate if further evaluation and/or special services may be needed. The screenings will be in the following developmental areas: Vision, Hearing, Speech, Language, Motor Skills, Social/Emotional and Learning.
To schedule your child for an appointment, please call Cherie Patterson with the Cosmopolis School District Office at 360-532-7181.

The most important thing to know about the P-EBT Emergency School Meals Program is that all students who were enrolled in the Cosmopolis School District at the time of the closure in March are eligible for up to $399 to buy groceries. Watch for more information to come out this month.

Families that don't already have a Basic Food EBT card from the state will need to apply to receive their P-EBT debit card. The site will open later this month. The flow chart below explains more.

Watch for more information to be handed out with breakfast and lunch at the Food Service sites next week.

post_text:
Student Donations Needed!

Cosmopolis Elementary and Wishkah Elementary challenged each other to a friendly contest. The school with the highest student engagement with their learning during the school closure would be recognized and each student would receive a little prize. Don Hay, Dean of Students at Wishkah, graciously suggested that since both schools exceeded our expectations that together we celebrate their success. As of this post, Wishkah has had a 98.8% rate and Cosmopolis has had a 91.5% rate. Our contest ends this week.

I am calling on our area to help us recognize a total of 270 students by June 9, Cosmopolis‚Äôs last day of school. We are looking for small items, coupons, etc. that elementary students would enjoy. Our students have worked so hard during this challenging time. They have shown resilience, perseverance and courage. Way to go Wishkah Loggers and Cosmopolis Cougars! Please call Cherie Patterson, Cosmopolis Principal at 360-532-7181 or email cpatterson@cosmopolisschool.com if you can help us.

post_text: Congratulations to Mrs. Jeanette Mitchell who will retire at the end of this school year. Mrs. Mitchell has worked for more than a decade at Cosmopolis School teaching second graders and then this year volunteered to do a 1st/2nd grade split. Mrs. Mitchell's positive connections with students and families helped students succeed in her classroom. She expected students to grow not only academically but socially. She encouraged her students to be bucket fillers and not bucket dippers. Please help us congratulate Mrs. Mitchell on her upcoming retirement!
text: Congratulations to Mrs. Jeanette Mitchell who will retire at the end of this school year. Mrs. Mitchell has worked for more than a decade at Cosmopolis School teaching second graders and then this year volunteered to do a 1st/2nd grade split. Mrs. Mitchell's positive connections with students and families helped students succeed in her classroom. She expected students to grow not only academically but socially. She encouraged her students to be bucket fillers and not bucket dippers. Please help us congratulate Mrs. Mitchell on her upcoming retirement!

post_text:
May 4-8 is Teacher Appreciation Week. Cosmopolis School wants to recognize our staff for their dedication to our students planning lessons, meeting with students on Zoom during the day and evening hours, teaching lessons in ways they have not taught before and worrying about each student and their family as we go through this challenging time together.

We also want to recognize our parents this week too. We could not move forward with distance learning without you. Parents, we know you have been thrust into a teaching role without any formal training and we admire your willingness to partner with us as we all succeed for the benefit of our children.

This week we recognize the staff and parents during Teacher Appreciation Week! I appreciate and admire each of you.

Cherie Patterson, Cosmopolis School District Superintendent

Wanted! All new incoming students for this or next school year. The District is working on the budget for next year and needs to plan for how much staff will be needed given our growing population. Please register as soon as possible at https://www.cosmopolisschool.com/school/enrollment

Prior to September 1, children must be five years old to enter kindergarten and four years old to enter preschool. Children must be current on ALL immunizations before attending their first day of school so please plan ahead especially with the limited access to health care providers at this time. For more information, call 360-532-7181.
